title: Ask HN: Online Banking in Europe Without Smartphone
text:
Hello,

I am a bit troubled. I want to get rid of my smarthpone. But the banks i am using only offer the TAN generation via Apps. I can't even make a wire transfer from my computer without the app on my smartphone.

I am thinking about trying to build a relay service with an emulated android device or so that will read out that tan & send it me via SMS. I know this would probably require a lot of effort for this small task, but i don't see my bank or another bank switching back to SMS.

Or what else could i do? what would you do?

Show HN: A personal read-only localhost Twitter server (not client)
text: TweetsToRSS is a free personal Twitter webserver that runs on Android/Linux/Windows/Mac. It runs in the background as a localhost server and you can access it from any browser or RSS newsfeed reader program. TweetsToRSS generates rich RSS feeds and clutter-free web pages for Twitter. It is useful for those who don't have much to post and/or would like to (anonymously) follow Twitter users and topics. It is also great for archiving Twitter feeds on an e-mail client or RSS feed reader. TweetsToRSS server can create RSS feeds and web pages for any user timeline, hashtag or search query.
